ARGENTINA ' S EDENOR WANTS TO DOUBLE BOND PROGRAM . The board of directors at Argentina ' s electricity distribution company Edenor SA said Wednesday it had proposed to raise the amount of the company ' s negotiable bond program to $ 600 million from $ 300 million . In a statement to the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange , the company said it wanted to double its bond program to take advantage of favorable local and international bond market conditions to re - finance current liabilities more cheaply . Edenor said it would hold a shareholders ' meeting on September 5 to win approval for the increase . ( ( - - Axel Bugge , Buenos Aires Newsroom , 541 318 - 0668 ) ) 
